modules.description: Provides operations for reading from and writing to a key-value store using Unix file system directories as the backend. Works with string-based keys and values, and supports both read-only and read-write access. Used to persist and retrieve application state in MirageOS environments where a lightweight, file-backed store is required.

Provides operations to interact with a key-value store, including checking existence, retrieving values, listing entries, and modifying data with support for partial reads and writes. Works with keys of type `Mirage_kv.Key.t` and handles errors and write errors through dedicated types. Used for managing persistent data in a loopback file system, such as storing and updating configuration values or logs.
